Solly Makganoto JOHANNESBURG – The count down has begun for the much anticipated Leon Schuster movie, Frank and Fearless, which will open in 95 cinemas around the country on November 23rd. The movie is about an ageing reprobate, a rural African boy, a rottweiler, and an orphaned baby rhino who are all set on stopping rhino poaching. Their quest takes them through hysterical situations and tragic times, as they end up an inspiration and a conscience to a world in need of heroes. The star-studded cast, which includes Kenneth Nkosi, Khanyi Mbau, Jennifer Steyn and David Dennis and Themba Ntuli.  The Countdown has begun!! We have 3 days to till #FRANKANDFEARLESS is released in 95 cinemas across the country. Book your tickets now! You don’t want to miss it.
